<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Topic-Viable classes on a PvP server...</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Nafgar[CC]">Nafgar[CC]</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 1:47 a.m. 11/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Topic-Viable classes on a PvP server...<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>While every class will be needed and embraced on the public servers, the PvP server has serious considerations when choosing ones class. First of all, why in the world would you chose a character who cant

<BR>A. Gate/Teleport
<BR>B. Fight without armor
<BR>Point is, on the PvP server, it will be constant war. If you chose, lets say, a fighter, a pure and simple fighter, I expect you to die quick. Either you will die to 5 wizards ganking your ass, mana dumping everything into you. Or you will die while running through zones being chased by someone 4 levels above you. This does not make it a viable class. With a magic casting class you have the option of IMMEDIATLY gating and getting out of danger. NOT ONLY THAT, but you also have the fact that magic using classes keep their weapons(spells), forever.
<BR>I close with this thought. On the PvP server, will we only see monks and a crapload of halfling druids(you know everyone is gonna be one) and some wizards?? I think so, the others will be dead :)
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
